timelineItems.args:
{"crew":true,"message":"TO: USS PHOENIX
FROM: STARBASE 74

PHOENIX, BE SURE TO KEEP US UPDATED DURING YOUR MISSION. SEND US MESSAGES EVERY 10 MINUTES TELLING US WHAT YOU ARE DOING.

STARBASE 74 OUT","sender":"STARBASE 74"}

Send Message
Send Message
timelineItems.args:
{"crew":true,"message":"FROM: USS RANGER

Voyager, our engineer has completed his study of the sensor scans 
of the Pennae ship.  The power source is a single source quantum singularity.  It can produce tremendous power over many years.  We do not have the kind of techology necessary to make that kind of a power source.  The Pennou weapons could also be very powerful, so be careful.

USS Ranger out","sender":"USS Ranger"}

timelineItems.args:
{"crew":true,"message":"FROM: USS MONTGOMERY 

We are under heavy attack, our shields are no match for their weapons.  We have to abandon ship please send rescue ships.
We are ejecting our warp core and our records. 

USS Montgomery Out","sender":"USS Montgomery"}

types.name: Class I Probe
types.description: The smallest probe; can only hold 4 units of equipment. Use for probe networks and general purposes.

types.name: Class II Probe
types.description: This medium-sized probe can hold 10 units of equipment. Use for probe networks and general purposes.

types.name: Class III Probe
types.description: This is the largest standard probe. It can hold up to 16 units of equipment. Use for probe networks and general purposes.

types.name: Defensive Probe
types.description: This weapon-like probe has access to additional equipment. You can use it to defend your ship. It holds 20 units of equipment.

types.name: Science Probe
types.description: This probe can use special emitters and detectors for specific scientific experiments. It holds 12 units of equipment.

equipment.name: Probe Network Package
equipment.description: A probe network package instructs the probe to network with up to 7 other probes.

equipment.name: Radio Transceiver
equipment.description: A radio transceiver is used to let the probe communicate.

equipment.name: Video Camera
equipment.description: A Video Camera can take still or moving pictures.

equipment.name: Communications Signal Booster
equipment.description: A Communications Signal Booster gives the probe's radio more range.

equipment.name: Encoding Sequencer
equipment.description: Encodes and encrypts signals, making them more secure.

equipment.name: Extra Data Storage
equipment.description: Increases the amount of on-board data storage, allowing the probe to store more data.

equipment.name: Extra Fuel Cell
equipment.description: An Extra Fuel Cell lets the probe travel further and perform longer.

equipment.name: Sensor Array
equipment.description: The Sensor Array gives the probe general scanning abilities.

equipment.name: Chemical Analysis Package
equipment.description: A Chemical Analysis Package lets the probe research what chemicals it has found.

equipment.name: Sample Retrieval Package
equipment.description: A Sample Retrieval Package lets the probe get something and return it to the ship.

equipment.name: Radiation Shielding
equipment.description: Protects the probe from moderate levels of radiaiton.

equipment.name: ECM Package
equipment.description: An ECM (Electronic Counter Measures) Package is used to jam electronics.

equipment.name: Gas Giant Encounter Package
equipment.description: A Gas Giant Encounter Package allows the probe to research a gas giant.

equipment.name: Nebula Encounter Package
equipment.description: A Nebula Encounter Package allows the probe to research a nebula.

equipment.name: Planetary Encounter Package
equipment.description: A Planetary Encounter Package allows the probe to research a planet.

equipment.name: Decoy Package
equipment.description: A Decoy Package sends out signals to make sensor devices detect the probe as a ship.

equipment.name: Subspace Encounter Package
equipment.description: A Subspace Encounter Package allows the probe to research subspace.

equipment.name: Solar Encounter Package
equipment.description: A Solar Encounter Package allows the probe to research a star.

equipment.name: Transporter Relay
equipment.description: A transporter relay extends the transporter range of this ship.

equipment.name: Hologram Projector Package
equipment.description: A Hologram Projector Package makes the probe look like a ship.

equipment.name: Metaphasic Shield Generator
equipment.description: Shield Generator that can construct a Shield Grid with other probes up to 2,500 Km protecting from radiation.

equipment.name: Self-Destruct Kit
equipment.description: A Self-Destruct Kit allows the probe to receive a self-destruct signal from the station.

equipment.name: Warp Nacelle
equipment.description: A Warp Nacelle (warp core included) allows the probe to travel at warp speed.

equipment.name: Targeting Sensors
equipment.description: Targeting sensors extends the targeting range of the probe.

equipment.name: Proximity Destruct
equipment.description: A Proximity Self-Destruct detector tells the probe to blow-up when an enemy is near.

equipment.name: Titanium Armor Alloy
equipment.description: Titanium Armor Alloy increases the probe's defenses.

equipment.name: Stealth Field
equipment.description: A stealth field masks the probe making it harder to detect.

equipment.name: Phaser Head
equipment.description: A Phaser Head allows the probe to fire one phaser shot at an enemy ship.

equipment.name: Tachyon Emitter
equipment.description: A Tachyon Emitter allows the probe to interact with tachyon particles.

equipment.name: Resonance Emitter
equipment.description: A Resonance Emitter allows the probe to interact with resonating particles.

equipment.name: Lithium Emitter
equipment.description: A Lithium Emitter allows the probe to interact with lithium particles.

equipment.name: Carbon Emitter
equipment.description: A Carbon Emitter allows the probe to interact with carbon particles.

equipment.name: Radiation Emitter
equipment.description: A Radiation Emitter allows the probe to interact with radioactive particles.

equipment.name: Oxygen Emitter
equipment.description: An Oxygen Emitter allows the probe to interact with oxygen particles.

equipment.name: Hydrogen Emitter
equipment.description: A Hydrogen Emitter allows the probe to interact with hydrogen particles.

equipment.name: Helium Emitter
equipment.description: A Helium Emitter allows the probe to interact with helium particles.

equipment.name: Graviton Emitter
equipment.description: A Graviton Emitter allows the probe to interact with graviton particles.

equipment.name: Magnetic Emitter
equipment.description: A Magnetic Emitter allows the probe to interact with magnetic particles.
